Generates the context document for a whole directory rather than a single file — the counterpart to `summarizer-leaf.md` one level up the aggregation chain. It defines the rollup's role: orient a reader arriving at a subtree from above, using its `intent.md` plus the already-produced child `.ctx`/`rollup.ctx` files as sole inputs, so it must never re-derive facts from source directly.

Its binding contract with the rest of the pipeline is de-duplication: content already correctly stated in a child's `.ctx` must not reappear in the rollup, and this file spells out the adversarial re-read step used to enforce that. It also defines the `intent_divergence:` signal — a single-line, single-purpose escape hatch triggered only when the subtree's actual behavior contradicts its `intent.md`; the literal label matters because some downstream auditor greps for it. Coupled to `prompts/summarizer-leaf.md` (shared tone/rules, sibling in the same prompt family) and to `docs/SPEC.md`, which fixes the line budget referenced but not stated numerically here — if SPEC.md's budget changes, this file's "stay tight" guidance still holds but the enforced number lives elsewhere.